Subject: [PATCH 10/17] initrd: switch initrd loading to struct file based APIs
Date:   Thu,  9 Jul 2020 17:18:07 +0200
Message-Id: <20200709151814.110422-11-hch@lst.de>
X-Mailer: git-send-email 2.26.2
In-Reply-To: <20200709151814.110422-1-hch@lst.de>
References: <20200709151814.110422-1-hch@lst.de>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
X-SRS-Rewrite: SMTP reverse-path rewritten from <hch@infradead.org> by casper.infradead.org. See http://www.infradead.org/rpr.html
Sender: linux-fsdevel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-fsdevel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-fsdevel@vger.kernel.org

There is no good reason to mess with file descriptors from in-kernel
code, switch the initrd loading to struct file based read and writes
instead.

Signed-off-by: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
